<item>
            <title>[WICKET-6157] WicketTester and application servers are destroying app differently</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-6157</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It&apos;s easy to recieve NPE because of absence of App in context in test during destroying app and it&apos;s OK on real app. The reason is the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Wicket Test has just this code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;br/&gt;
	public void destroy()&lt;/p&gt;
	{
		application.internalDestroy();
		ThreadContext.detach();
	}
&lt;p&gt;```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But real filter has this one:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;```&lt;br/&gt;
@Override&lt;br/&gt;
	public void destroy()&lt;br/&gt;
	{&lt;br/&gt;
		if (application != null)&lt;br/&gt;
		{&lt;br/&gt;
			try&lt;/p&gt;
			{
				ThreadContext.setApplication(application);
				application.internalDestroy();
			}
&lt;p&gt;			finally&lt;/p&gt;
			{
				ThreadContext.detach();
				application = null;
			}
&lt;p&gt;		}&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;		if (applicationFactory != null)&lt;br/&gt;
		{&lt;br/&gt;
			try&lt;/p&gt;
			{
				applicationFactory.destroy(this);
			}
&lt;p&gt;			finally&lt;/p&gt;
			{
				applicationFactory = null;
			}
&lt;p&gt;		}&lt;br/&gt;
	}&lt;br/&gt;
```&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So, as you can see filter explicitly setting app, so NPE would not happen, but wicket tester do not. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
